text: Katariina Tamm (born March 2, 1989) is an Estonian actress. She graduated from the theater class of the Tallinn Old Town College of Education in 2007. In 2011 she graduated from the Turku Art Academy, majoring in puppetry. In 2019 she obtained a master's degree at the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art. She then worked at the Estonian Youth Theatre, and then at the Von Krahl Theater in Talinn. ==References== Category:Estonian movie actors Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Estonian stage actors Category:Puppeteers
